<dl id="n03124b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03124b">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03124b"> 124(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> showed kindness <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n03124b"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Charles Lamb <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> gentleness to his sister Mary, &ldquo;Bridget Elia,&rdquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> His <mark>kindness</mark> was no doubt enhanced by her unfortunate fits of insanity and by the fact that in one those fits she had killed her mother. <small> Albert Mordell, <a name="AMEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AMEM"><cite title="source">The Erotic Motive in Literature</cite></a> (1919) 59</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
